20:23.597 --> 20:26.839
How come y'all ain't scared of us
like you was of Dally?

20:27.017 --> 20:30.305
Oh, you two are too sweet-looking
to scare anyone.

20:30.479 --> 20:33.141
Besides, I know about Dallas Winston.

20:34.150 --> 20:35.981
You two don't look mean.

20:36.152 --> 20:39.986
Yeah, right.
We're young and innocent.

20:40.156 --> 20:42.989
No. You're just not dirty.

20:43.159 --> 20:45.445
Come on, Dal's OK.
I mean, he's tough and all.

20:45.619 --> 20:48.486
But he's a cool old guy,
if you get to know him.

20:48.664 --> 20:50.700
He'd leave you alone
if he knew who you were.

20:50.875 --> 20:54.834
- Well, I'm glad he doesn't know us.
- I kind of admire him.

20:57.423 --> 20:59.084
Oi, Greaser! You're dead!

20:59.258 --> 21:01.044
What's he doing?
Get out of my hair!

21:01.218 --> 21:03.675
Hey, what have you done?

21:03.846 --> 21:06.212
Here, kid, have a beer.
It'll settle your nerves.

21:06.390 --> 21:11.305
Well, now, who we got here?
Your great-grandmothers, huh?

21:11.479 --> 21:14.687
What are you two young ladies
hanging out with these Greasers?

21:14.857 --> 21:16.813
Dal was bothering them.

21:16.984 --> 21:18.099
- He was, huh?
- Yeah.

21:18.277 --> 21:20.268
Where is old Dal now anyway?

21:21.906 --> 21:23.271
Yeah, where is old Dally?

21:26.285 --> 21:27.570
He left, Tim.

21:29.288 --> 21:31.700
Hey, I know he slashed my tyres!

21:32.792 --> 21:35.158
Look, Tim, he left.
He's not here. Really.

21:35.336 --> 21:37.998
- You guys seen Dally?
- No, no.

21:40.674 --> 21:42.710
Yeah, well, I'll be looking for him.

21:46.096 --> 21:48.838
- Dally got a blade?
- I don't think so.

21:49.016 --> 21:51.723
Good deal. Tim will fight fair
as long as he don't.

21:54.146 --> 21:56.728
You guys don't believe in playing rough,
do you?

21:56.899 --> 22:00.357
- Well, a fair fight ain't rough.
- Yeah, boy. Real simple!

22:00.528 --> 22:04.612
Yeah! If he gets killed or something,
you just bury him. No sweat!

22:06.325 --> 22:10.409
- You dig, OK, baby. You want a chew?
- Come on, Two-Bit.

22:10.579 --> 22:12.570
Help yourself.
Put hair on your chest!

22:14.208 --> 22:16.915
Ponyboy, come with me
and get some Cokes and popcorn.

22:17.086 --> 22:18.496
Sure.

22:18.671 --> 22:20.161
- Y'all want some?
- I do.

22:20.339 --> 22:24.048
Yeah, me, too.
Get Johnny some, too. I'm buying.

22:24.218 --> 22:25.458
Here you go.

22:27.888 --> 22:31.096
Your friend, the one with the sideburns,
is he OK?

22:31.267 --> 22:33.974
Yeah, he ain't dangerous,
if that's what you mean.

22:35.938 --> 22:38.224
- Hey, what are you doing?
- Hey, man!

22:38.899 --> 22:40.685
He sure scared Johnny.

22:41.861 --> 22:44.227
Johnny's a nervous wreck anyway.

22:44.405 --> 22:47.693
He got beat up a few months ago
by some Soc.

22:49.326 --> 22:51.442
Is that how he got his scar?

22:51.620 --> 22:53.702
Yeah, the guy was wearing a few rings.

22:56.709 --> 22:58.665
- Not all of us are like that.
- Sure.

22:58.836 --> 23:02.294
That's like saying all you Greasers
are like Dallas Winston.

23:02.464 --> 23:04.830
- Leave him, will you?
- What you gonna do about it?

23:05.009 --> 23:07.546
Let's take it outside.
That's what I'll do.

23:07.720 --> 23:11.212
All right, you two.
Why don't you both take it outside?

23:11.390 --> 23:13.802
Well, he's jumped a few people.

23:14.727 --> 23:18.515
Anyway, you think the Socs
have it made.

23:18.689 --> 23:22.432
The rich kids. The southside Soc.

23:22.610 --> 23:25.067
Well, I'll tell you something, Ponyboy,

23:25.237 --> 23:29.150
and it might come as a surprise,
but things are rough all over.

23:31.160 --> 23:33.276
Come on. Let's get out of here.

23:33.454 --> 23:35.661
Or Two-Bit will think
we eloped to Mexico!

23:37.458 --> 23:40.416
- So, you're from the southside, huh?
- Yes.

23:40.586 --> 23:43.419
- It must be a nice neighbourhood.
- It is. I like it.

23:43.589 --> 23:45.125
- Do you?
- Mm-hm.

23:45.299 --> 23:48.257
Yeah, I'm...
I'm from the other side of town.

24:10.157 --> 24:14.196
Tell me about your oldest brother.
You never seem to talk about him.

24:14.370 --> 24:16.782
What's to tell?

24:16.956 --> 24:19.117
He's big and roofs houses.

24:19.291 --> 24:21.373
No, really. I mean, what's he like?

24:21.543 --> 24:24.034
I feel like I know Soda
for as much as you talk about him.

24:24.213 --> 24:26.704
Tell me about Darry.
Is he wild and reckless like Soda?

24:26.882 --> 24:28.873
Or dreamy like you?

24:31.261 --> 24:34.173
He ain't like Soda,
and he sure ain't like me!

24:34.348 --> 24:36.179
He can't stand me!

24:37.476 --> 24:41.264
I bet he wishes he could stick me
in some boys' home. Soda won't let him.

24:41.438 --> 24:44.680
- What are you talking about?
- Come on. You all get along fine.

24:44.858 --> 24:48.316
No, we don't! You shut your trap,
cos you ain't wanted at home either!

24:48.487 --> 24:49.977
You shut your mouth, kid!

24:51.323 --> 24:53.279
I'm sorry. I got a little mad.

24:53.450 --> 24:55.281
Don't worry about it.

24:55.452 --> 24:58.740
- We couldn't get along without you.
- Marcia!

24:58.914 --> 25:01.621
- Look who's coming!
- What are we gonna do?

25:01.792 --> 25:04.659
- Just act normal. Just keep calm.
- Who are these clowns?

25:06.839 --> 25:08.545
Cherry, what's going on?

25:08.716 --> 25:10.331
What are you doing?

25:12.594 --> 25:14.630
Just because we got a little drunk...

25:14.805 --> 25:17.968
You call reeling and passing out
on the streets "a little"?

25:18.142 --> 25:19.427
Bob, I've told you before,

25:19.601 --> 25:22.343
I'm never going out with you
when you're drinking!

25:22.521 --> 25:25.354
That's no reason to go walking the streets
with these bums!

25:25.524 --> 25:27.480
- Who are you calling bums, pal?
- You!

25:27.651 --> 25:30.484
- Randy!
- We got two more in the back seat.

25:31.530 --> 25:33.862
- Pity the back seat!
- If you're looking for a fight...

25:34.033 --> 25:37.116
I am looking for a fight!
Let's go! Come on! Right not!

25:37.286 --> 25:38.776
Come on!

25:38.954 --> 25:41.115
All right! We'll go with you!
Just wait a minute!

25:41.290 --> 25:45.374
- We ain't scared of these bastards!
- I hate fights! I hate 'em!

25:46.336 --> 25:47.951
Come here, Ponyboy.

25:51.050 --> 25:53.166
I'm sorry.

25:53.343 --> 25:56.426
Look, I couldn't use this.
I could never cut no one.

25:56.597 --> 25:58.053
Cherry! Come on!

25:58.223 --> 26:00.179
We'd better go with 'em.

26:05.731 --> 26:09.349
If I see you in school and I don't say hi,
don't take it personal, OK?

26:09.526 --> 26:11.062
Yeah, I know.

26:11.236 --> 26:13.818
Really. You're a nice boy and everything.

26:13.989 --> 26:15.525
It's OK.

26:21.288 --> 26:23.404
I hope I never see Dallas Winston again.

26:23.582 --> 26:26.119
If I do,
I'll probably fall in love with him.

26:26.293 --> 26:28.079
- Come on, baby.
- Don't touch me!

26:29.922 --> 26:31.753
<i>Blue moon</i>

26:31.924 --> 26:36.338
<i>You saw me standing alone</i>

26:37.554 --> 26:39.010
<i>Without a dream in my heart...</i>

26:39.181 --> 26:43.140
- Just watch it, greaseball.
- Says who?

26:43.310 --> 26:45.141
<i>Without a love of my own...</i>

26:45.312 --> 26:47.849
Boy, those are two of the
best-looking girls I've ever seen.

26:49.608 --> 26:50.973
Yeah.

26:55.823 --> 26:58.235
- What was that?
- Marcia's number.

26:58.408 --> 26:59.864
Probably a phoney one, too.

27:00.035 --> 27:02.321
I must have been out of my mind
to ask for it.

27:02.496 --> 27:04.703
Girl like that would never
go out with me, anyway.

27:04.873 --> 27:06.363
Where are y'all going?

27:06.542 --> 27:07.907
- Home.
- Whoa!

27:09.211 --> 27:10.951
Here! I got me a new hat!

27:13.882 --> 27:15.588
You're crazy!

27:15.759 --> 27:19.422
I don't why I handed you that busted bottle.
You never would have used it.

27:19.596 --> 27:21.507
I might have. Where you headed?

27:21.682 --> 27:24.424
I don't know.
Maybe I'll go play snooker or get drunk.

27:24.601 --> 27:26.432
- I'll see you later!
- OK!

27:28.147 --> 27:31.184
I hate when my folks are fighting.
Let's go to the lot.

27:36.738 --> 27:40.401
<i>Blue moon</i>

27:40.576 --> 27:43.033
<i>You saw me standing alone...</i>

27:43.203 --> 27:45.285
It was because we're Greasers, Pone.

27:47.749 --> 27:50.741
Might have hurt her reputation
or something, that's all.

27:50.919 --> 27:52.830
Don't worry about it.

27:53.005 --> 27:54.791
Yeah, I guess so.

28:05.517 --> 28:08.099
Man, that was a tough car, huh?

28:10.522 --> 28:13.559
Mustangs, they're tough.

28:14.735 --> 28:16.851
Big-time Socs, all right.

28:17.946 --> 28:19.857
It's always the same.

28:22.034 --> 28:26.403
<i>Blue moon</i>

28:31.460 --> 28:35.624
<i>You saw me standing alone...</i>

28:35.797 --> 28:38.539
I can't take much more of this, Ponyboy!

28:38.717 --> 28:41.925
